Step 1: Identify the Operating Cash Flow from the Cash Flow statement.
• Operating Cash Flow ("Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities") = 116257.19

Step 2: Identify the Total Current Liabilities from the Balance Sheet at the End Date.
• Total Current Liabilities = 967271.87

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio.
• Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities = 116257.19 / 967271.87 ≈ 0.1203

Step 4: Rounding the ratio to two decimal places gives 0.12.

Thus, the solution is:
